cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with energy-efficient scheduling in a multiuser setting with time-varying channel qualities, which is a common problem in wireless communication networks. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The problem is formulated as a Markov Decision Problem, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm that outperforms existing strategies, which is related to machine learning and optimization, and thus could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
